Tragedy struck Chepkongony village in Uasin Gishu county on Saturday after two school-going children drowned in a dam while washing  clothes. Victims were a 17-year-old Form Four student at Kaptumo Secondary School and a 10 -year-old Class Four pupil at Rotuga Primary School. The deceased are close family members and according to residents, they had gone to the dam to wash clothes. Eldoret East Police boss John Owouth said the high school girl dived into the dam in an effort to save the 10-year old, who had slipped into the dam while fetching water, but unfortunately they both drowned. Owouth said residents managed to retrieve one of the bodies on Sunday while the other was retrieved yesterday.  Bodies were taken to the Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital mortuary.